[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Model drift monitoring.** Patient populations shift (new admission patterns, protocol changes, staffing differences). The model was trained on historical data that may not represent current practice. You need continuous monitoring of feature distributions, recommendation acceptance rates, and outcome metrics, with automated alerts when drift exceeds thresholds. On AWS, use SageMaker Model Monitor to track feature distribution drift against training data baselines, and CloudWatch custom metrics for clinician agreement rate and safety filter override rate. Alert when features drift beyond 2 standard deviations for sustained periods (4+ hours in an ICU context).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Model rollback strategy.** Use SageMaker production variants to run shadow traffic: both old and new policies receive the same patient states, but only the validated model's recommendations are surfaced. Monitor the agreement rate between old and new models. Define a rollback trigger (e.g., clinician override rate exceeds 50% for 48 hours, or safety filter override rate doubles). When triggered, shift 100% of traffic back to the previous model variant via UpdateEndpointWeightsAndCapacities, which completes in seconds without endpoint downtime.
